    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Joints between two separately cast metal elements in which one element slots into the hollow “sleeve” of the other. The joint is generally further secured using pins, rivets, or by soldering.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
